cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the embedding of conditional logics into classical higher-order logic, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic and computation (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the automation of reasoning within and about conditional logics, which is a topic that is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of automated theorem provers and model finders also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on reasoning and automation makes it relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
